body: In particular, we should make sure names are pub-friendly:

comment_data.body: Putting on-deck as it's hit a few folks (besides me!) --- see #687.

We already do some of this in `flutter create`, maybe it should do more?
https://github.com/flutter/flutter/blob/master/packages/flutter_tools/lib/src/commands/create.dart#L179

Good thinking @eseidelGoogle.  Probably we should.  The rub here is that we've already created the project in IntelliJ when we call `flutter create` so it will just bomb out on us when run.  A better flow would be live validation in the wizard (e.g., before running `create`).  IOW: I think we probably need validation in both places unfortunately.  But anyway, yeah, both validations should totally agree!
Forward pointer:  Section "16.33 Identifier Reference" of the [Dart language spec](http://www.ecma-international.org/publications/files/ECMA-ST/ECMA-408.pdf) has the grammar we want to crib.
Not yet.  My PR is hung up on build issues.  It's also won't do anything in the context of WebStorm and other "small IDEs". I'll do some more poking later this week.
